[1] OIE report
Date: Fri 17 Jun 2011
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly
disease information 2011; 24(25) [edited]
http://web.oie.int/wahis/public.php?page=single_report&pop=1&reportid=10704


Foot-and-mouth disease, Mozambique
----------------------------------
Information received on (and dated) 17 Jun 2011 from Dr Florencia A
Massango Cipriano, director, Veterinary Services, National Directorate
of Veterinary Services, Maputo, Mozambique

Summary
Report type: follow-up report no 4
Start date: 24 Sep 2010
Date of 1st confirmation of the event: 30 Sep 2010
Date submitted to OIE: 17 Jun 2011
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 23 Aug 2003
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Foot and mouth disease virus
Serotype: SAT 2
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (basic), laboratory
(advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1 (01/MZ/11): Lumane, Chicumbane, Xai-Xai, Gaza
Date of start of the outbreak: 20 May 2011
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: village
Affected animals
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 2000 / 7 / 0 / 0 / 0
Affected population: cattle of all sex and ages

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: illegal movement of
animals; contact with infected animal(s) at grazing/watering; fomites
(humans, vehicles, feed, etc.)
Epidemiological comments: 8 previously reported outbreaks have been
resolved. No clinical cases of the disease have been observed in the
area of these outbreaks in the last 4 months.

Control measures
Measures applied: quarantine; movement control inside the country;
screening; zoning; vaccination in response to the outbreak(s);
disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s); no treatment of
affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

--
