******
[2] News report
Date: Wed 15 Jun 2011
Source: Afriquinfos, Xinhua News Agency report [in French, trans.
Mod.MPP, edited]
http://www.afriquinfos.com/articles/2011/6/15/brevesdafrique-180193.asp


Local media reported Wednesday [15 Jun 2011] that cases of FMD were
detected in Xai Xai, the capital of Gaza province in southern
Mozambique, saying the disease had hit the city and its suburbs.

According to health authorities, the disease was detected over the
weekend, and all movements of cattle have been suspended. FMD has
previously affected the Macia and Chicualacuala districts of Gaza.

However, the authorities had declared [the disease] under control by
late May [2011]. The authorities told the media that a livestock
vaccination campaign was launched in the affected areas on Tuesday [14
Jun 2011].

"The situation is no longer worrisome" said Jose Muamba at the
directorate of health in Xai Xai, quoted by the report.

Mr Muamba also called on people to bring their cattle to vaccination
centers. He also warned that those who violate this injunction would
be severely punished.

--
communicated by:
ProMED-FRA
